title: Volleyball Roundup: Barons lose in tourney play
text:
Volleyball Roundup: Barons lose in tourney play 8:27 p.m. EDT October 19, 2015 CONNECT TWEET LINKEDIN COMMENT EMAIL MORE 
Granville 3, Buckeye Valley 0 
The Barons lost at Granville Monday in Division II district tournament play 25-10, 25-19 and 25-17. 
No other info was reported. 
North Union 3, Northmor 0 
The Wildcats won in the three sets on Saturday over the Golden Knights 25-23, 25-7 and 25-19. 
North Union was led by Jordyn Zoll with 13 assists, 6 digs, 3 kills and 2 aces. Anna Donner also had an ace while adding 13 digs, Karlee Carroll had 8 digs and 4 kills while Lindsey Wiseman added 7 digs. 
Galion 3, Centerburg 1 
The Tigers won at home on Saturday against Centerburg 17-25, 26-24, 25-21 and 25-14. 
Renee Lemke led Galion with 30 assists, 20 digs, 3 aces and 3 kills while Alaina Wright had 7 kills, 11 digs, 2 blocks and an ace. Emily Garber added 13 kills and a block; Skylar LeMaster had 6 kills and 12 digs. Read or Share this story: http://ohne.ws/1LHjoKT MORE STORIES
